<TEXT>

<s docid="FBIS4-36917" num="13"> BFN [Text] Responding to a question regarding a news report published in a local English daily alleging the expulsion of two Pakistani diplomats from Germany, a Foreign Office spokesman said in Islamabad today that the report by German television was factually incorrect.</s>

<s docid="FBIS4-36917" num="14"> No Pakistani diplomat has been expelled from Germany as asserted in the report.</s>

<s docid="FBIS4-36917" num="15"> The spokesman said Pakistan is procuring a number of sophisticated items of [as heard] equipment from various sources.</s>

<s docid="FBIS4-36917" num="16"> Normally, it is for supplier companies to obtain export license for restricted items.</s>

<s docid="FBIS4-36917" num="17"> For its part, Pakistan seeks to scrupulously observe the export laws of the concerned countries.</s>

<s docid="FBIS4-36917" num="18"> He said the report appears to be an attempt to sensationalize normal transactions.</s>
</TEXT>
